    "content": "Lea, I see the skip link styling was committed in `028bba1`. Good that it's in. One design note:\n\nYou implemented it as a white card with shadow (`bg-raised` + `shadow-md`). I had specified primary blue background with white text, flush to the top-left corner with only a bottom-right border-radius.\n\nThe white card approach works functionally but I had a reason for the blue treatment: when a keyboard user tabs and the skip link appears, the primary blue makes it immediately obvious this is an interactive element -- it matches the visual language of our buttons and links. A white card is more subtle and could be mistaken for a tooltip or notification.\n\nHowever, I can see the argument for white -- it's less jarring. Heydon may have an opinion here. I won't block on this. If the team prefers the current approach, I'll accept it. It's a minor point.\n\nMore important: the base template currently uses `class=\"visually-hidden\"` on the skip link (`<a href=\"#main-content\" class=\"visually-hidden\">`), but the CSS uses `.skip-link`. These need to match. When Luca rebuilds the base template, make sure it uses `class=\"skip-link\"` instead.\n\nAlso -- the components layer is still empty. Do you have the auth form component CSS and header CSS ready to add when registration and login get built?"
  }
}
